edu.ncsu.csc216.tracker.requirement

Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.tracker.requirement.Command

  • public class Command
extends java.lang.Object
    Command class is the class that is used to update the Requirement state. It uses the FSM design pattern to error check before it is used in Requirement class.
    Author:
    jhnguye4

    • Constructor Detail

      • Command

        public Command(CommandValue command,
               java.lang.String summary,
               java.lang.String acceptanceTestId,
               int priority,
               java.lang.String estimate,
               java.lang.String developerId,
               Rejection rejectionReason)
        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Constructor for Command object that has seven parameters that will have a value or null depending on which RequirementState it is in and what information is needed to update the Requirement.
        Parameters:
        command - is the Command object
        summary - String of the summary for the requirement, shoulder never be empty or null
        acceptanceTestId - String of the acceptanceTestId for the requirement, shoulder never be empty or null
        priority - int of the priority for the Requirement, will be 0 in submitted and rejected state but 1-3 other states
        estimate - String that is null in submitted state but is edited in accepted state
        developerId - String of developer that is set in the working state
        rejectionReason - Rejection object of the Requirement when in Rejected state.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
